    <stitle>DT 466 / DT 570 / HT 570 Service Manual - 2004 Emissions with EGR - Front Cover and Related Components -
        Inspection - Oil Pump Side and End Clearance
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc graphiccount="2">
        <title>Oil Pump Side and End Clearance</title>
        <figure id="f2650633" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figeg8/eg8653.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
            <caption>Oil pump outer gear side clearance</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">With a film of oil coating the outer wall of the outer rotor, measure the oil pump side
                clearance by placing a feeler gauge between the oil pump housing and outer rotor.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f2650634" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figeg8/eg8655.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
            <caption>Gerotor oil pump end clearance</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Place a straightedge across the gerotor oil pump surface. Measure end clearance by sliding a
                feeler gauge between the straightedge and gerotor assembly.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Compare measurements with
                <hotlnk document="eges2651_142.xml" xrefid="t2650601" appearance="hottext">specifications</hotlnk>.
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
